## 🚫 BLOCKER #1: Missing `parseManifest` — no camelCase→snake_case mapping

**Root cause of 3 BLOCKER and 1 MUST FIX.** The new `loader.ts` reads `soul.json` via a direct JSON cast instead of a field-mapping `parseManifest` as the reference does.

### Evidence

**`loader.ts:84`** — no parseManifest call:

```ts
const manifest = yield * readJsonFile<SoulManifest>(fs, manifestPath);
```

**`soul-fs.ts:27-33`** — `readJsonFile` does a raw `JSON.parse` + cast:

```ts
return fs.readFileString(soulPath).pipe(
  Effect.flatMap((content: string) =>
    Effect.try({
      try: () => JSON.parse(content) as T, // <-- DIRECT CAST
      catch: (cause) => new ManifestParseError({ path: soulPath, cause }),
    }),
  ),
);
```

### Reference vs current

The reference `src/.source/soul.ts:342-483` (`parseManifest`) maps every camelCase JSON field to its snake_case TS counterpart. **These 15+ mappings are entirely missing from the new loader:**

| camelCase JSON field (spec)                 | snake_case TS field                  | Reference map (line)      |
| ------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------- |
| `specVersion`                               | `spec_version`                       | `.source/soul.ts:458`     |
| `displayName`                               | `display_name`                       | `.source/soul.ts:460`     |
| `allowedTools`                              | `allowed_tools`                      | `.source/soul.ts:468`     |
| `recommendedSkills` / `skills` (legacy)     | `recommended_skills`                 | `.source/soul.ts:361-373` |
| `files.userTemplate`                        | `files.user_template`                | `.source/soul.ts:383`     |
| `supersededBy`                              | `superseded_by`                      | `.source/soul.ts:474`     |
| `interactionMode`                           | `interaction_mode`                   | `.source/soul.ts:477`     |
| `compatibility.minTokenContext`             | `compatibility.min_token_context`    | `.source/soul.ts:357`     |
| `hardwareConstraints.*`                     | `hardware_constraints.*`             | `.source/soul.ts:402-411` |
| `safety.physical.contactPolicy`             | `safety.physical.contact_policy`     | `.source/soul.ts:419`     |
| `safety.physical.emergencyProtocol`         | `safety.physical.emergency_protocol` | `.source/soul.ts:420`     |
| `safety.physical.operatingZone`             | `safety.physical.operating_zone`     | `.source/soul.ts:421`     |
| `safety.physical.maxSpeed`                  | `safety.physical.max_speed`          | `.source/soul.ts:422`     |
| `sensors` (keyed object `{"lidar": {...}}`) | `Sensor[]` (array with `name`)       | `.source/soul.ts:429-440` |
| `actuators` (keyed object)                  | `Actuator[]` (array with `name`)     | `.source/soul.ts:443-455` |
| `hardwareConstraints.mobility` (string)     | `mobility: Mobility` (enum)          | `.source/soul.ts:408`     |
| `environment` (string)                      | `environment: Environment` (enum)    | `.source/soul.ts:476`     |

### Impact

Any spec-compliant `soul.json` using camelCase field names will have **all of the above fields silently set to `undefined`**. The manifest will appear to load without error but will be unusable — names, descriptions, display names, licenses, versions, and all embodied agent fields will be missing.

### Fix required

Add a `parseManifest` equivalent — either as a separate function in `loader.ts` or as a new exported function in `soul-fs.ts`. It must:

1. Map every camelCase JSON field to its snake_case TS counterpart
2. Apply defaults for optional fields (see BLOCKER #2)
3. Handle legacy `skills: string[]` format (see BLOCKER #3)
4. Convert keyed sensor/actuator objects to arrays (see MUST FIX #4)
5. Map string enum values to TS enum members
6. Return `SoulManifest`-typed result

